0_15	0.0	Under most circumstances, people who do the damage are not exempt from possible penalties unless they get a federal permit allowing them to "take," or harm a species.
0_16	0.5	But the ESA does not extend the penalties to 263 threatened species, including many of the listed salmon stocks in the Pacific Northwest.
0_17	0.0	(Threatened species are defined as likely to become endangered within the foreseeable future).
0_18	0.3333333333333333	In Washington, Oregon, Idaho and California, 20 of the 26 salmon populations listed under the ESA are threatened.
0_19	0.0	The other six are endangered.
0_20	0.2777777777777778	The Fish and Wildlife Service, the federal agency primarily responsible for enforcing the ESA, wrote regulations that make penalties identical for threatened and endangered species.
0_21	0.2857142857142857	But the Fisheries Service, which enforces the ESA for salmon, has no such regulations.
0_22	0.0	Instead the agency decides when crafting rules for individual listings whether harming a threatened species should carry ESA penalties.
0_23	0.0	The Fisheries Service's announcement on Dec.
0_24	0.0	14 was the first indication that the agency intends to require penalties under new rules for 14 threatened salmon stocks.
