14_1	1.0555555555555556	_ Operators of three Columbia River dams have agreed with the Clinton administration on a 50-year preservation plan that may provide a model for how the Pacific Northwest goes about saving its endangered salmon.
14_2	0.875	The major requirement is that the dams be operated with no net loss of salmon.
14_3	0.0	It is the product of four years of negotiations involving dam-owning utilities, the National Marine Fisheries Service, Indian tribes and a key conservation group.
